# App Startup Test Cases

| Test Case ID | TC\_SUCCESS\_STARTUP\_01 |
| :---- | :---- |
| Test Description | Verify application starts up properly when API is ready |
| Pre-Conditions | A functioning internet connection A working web browser with Javascript enabled |
| Test Steps | Start the development server with `npm run dev` Visit the url [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173)  |
| Test Data (if any) | NIL |
| Post-Conditions | The app’s loading screen appears while the app is loading An interactive map with a set of controls are displayed after the app fully loads, with the map centred on New York |
| Expected Result | As per post-conditions. |
| Actual Result | App’s loading screen appears while app is loading ![][image1] App fully loads with an interactive map and controls displayed ![][image2] |
| Test Case Status | PASS |

| Test Case ID | TC\_ERROR\_STARTUP\_02 |
| :---- | :---- |
| Test Description | Verify that errors encountered by the application while starting up is displayed to the user |
| Pre-Conditions | A functioning internet connection A working web browser with Javascript enabled |
| Test Steps | Introduce a typo into the URL of the API being called by editing the contents of the variable API\_BASE\_URL to “https://nyc-bus-engine-k3q4yvzczq-an.a.run.app/api/bus\_tri” in the commons.jsx file. Save the commons.jsx file Start the development server with the command `npm run dev`. Open the web application by visiting [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) in a browser. Click the “Ok” button at the bottom right of the displayed error modal. |
| Test Data (if any) | NIL |
| Post-Conditions | The app should display the map with an overlaid modal indicating that an error has occurred with the error message “Failed to fetch”. The “Ok” button on the bottom right of the modal should close the modal when clicked. |
| Expected Result | As per post-conditions. |
| Actual Result | Overlaid error modal is displayed with the error message “Failed to fetch” ![][image3] Clicking the “Ok” button closes the error modal. ![][image4] |
| Test Case Status | PASS |

# Options Population Test Cases

| Test Case ID | TC\_SUCCESS\_VEHREF\_OPT\_01 |
| :---- | :---- |
| Test Description | Verify successful retrieval of dropdown options when user chooses to search for bus trips by vehicle reference |
| Pre-Conditions | A functional internet connection A working web browser with Javascript enabled |
| Test Steps | Start the development server with `npm run dev` Open the app by visiting [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) Select the “By Vehicle Reference” button. Open the dropdown menu by clicking on the dropdown arrow Select the option “NYCT\_1210” |
| Test Data (if any) | Option to be selected: NYCT\_1210 |
| Post-Conditions | The dropdown menu should display all vehicle reference numbers sorted in ascending alphabetical order. The selected option should appear in the input field. The “By Vehicle Reference” button should have a blue fill with white text. |
| Expected Result | The dropdown menu should display all vehicle reference numbers in sorted order, starting from “NYCT\_1200” and ending with “NYCT\_9674”. The option “NYCT\_1210” should appear in the input field after being selected from the dropdown menu. The “By Vehicle Reference” button should have a blue fill with white text. |
| Actual Result | Dropdown menu shows vehicle reference numbers sorted in ascending alphabetical order. ![][image5]![][image6] The option “NYCT\_1210” is displayed in the input field after being selected from the dropdown me The “By Vehicle Reference” button is filled blue with white text. ![][image7]  |
| Test Case Status | PASS |

| Test Case ID | TC\_ERROR\_VEHREF\_OPT\_02 |
| :---- | :---- |
| Test Description | Verify display of error message upon the app’s failure to retrieve list of vehicle references to populate dropdown menu when user chooses to search for bus trips by vehicle reference number. |
| Pre-Conditions | A functional internet connection A working web browser with Javascript enabled |
| Test Steps | Introduce a typo into the contents of the variable VEH\_REF in commons.jsx by setting the variable equal to the string “/getVehRe” Start the development server with `npm run dev` Open the app by visiting [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) Select the “By Vehicle Reference” button. Click the “Ok” button in the modal that pops up. |
| Test Data (if any) | NIL |
| Post-Conditions | A modal with the error message “An error occurred while fetching options” should be overlaid on top of the map. Clicking the “Ok” button in the modal that pops up should close the modal. The “By Vehicle Reference” button should have a transparent fill and blue text/outline. |
| Expected Result | As per post-conditions. |
| Actual Result | A modal with the error message “An error occurred while fetching options” is overlaid on top of the map. ![][image8] Clicking the “Ok” button in error modal closes the modal. The “By Vehicle Reference” button is unselected i.e. has a transparent fill and blue text/line. ![][image9] |
| Test Case Status | PASS |

# Query Submission Test Cases

| Test Case ID | TC\_VALID\_VEHREF\_QUERY\_01 |
| :---- | :---- |
| Test Description | Verify that bus trips are properly plotted on the map upon user’s submission of a query to find bus trips by a user-specified vehicle reference number. |
| Pre-Conditions | A functional internet connection A working web browser with Javascript enabled |
| Test Steps | Start the development server with `npm run dev` Open the app by visiting [http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173) Select the “By Vehicle Reference” button. Open the dropdown menu by clicking on the dropdown arrow Select the option “NYCT\_1207” Click on the “Query” button. Click on the topmost marker. Click on the horizontal blue line close to the topmost marker. |
| Test Data (if any) | Option to be selected: NYCT\_1207 |
| Post-Conditions | Relevant routes should be plotted on the map in blue, while relevant points should be plotted on the map with a marker. Clicking on a marker should display the properties of the point in a pop-up. Clicking on a route should display the properties of the line in a pop-up. |
| Expected Result | Correct routes and points should be plotted on the map in blue, as shown below. ![][image13] Rest are as per pre-conditions. |
| Actual Result | Relevant points and routes are plotted on the map correctly. ![][image14] Clicking on a marker creates a pop-up with information on the properties of the point. ![][image15] Clicking on a route creates a pop-up with information on the properties of the route. ![][image16] |
| Test Case Status | PASS |
